```

## Alternative Designs

Since the model binders + providers are so similar to those for `DateTime`, @TanayParikh [raised the question](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/pull/45243#discussion_r1029935922) of whether it would be better to generalize the model binding for `DateTime`, `DateOnly`, and `TimeOnly`. This would allow maintenance and refactoring to be much cleaner and efficient for these very similar types. I think there's merit to this idea particularly at the model binder level (with each having their own provider) but since this would modify an existing public API, I am concerned about raising breaking changes.

## Risks

The addition of these new model binder providers to MVC option configuration (see [here](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/ed90b058fe349fec522eb40196f6902088539080/src/Mvc/Mvc.Core/src/Infrastructure/MvcCoreMvcOptionsSetup.cs#L77-L78)) would slightly increase the size of the [provider list in the MVC configuration class](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/f52ae1f2e40b78fdb84c4022af04e157cf503c38/src/Mvc/Mvc.Core/src/MvcOptions.cs#L46) but the expected difference is minimal.

